
<h2>Sign up</h2>

<%= form_for(resource, :as => resource_name, :url => registration_path(resource_name)) do |f| %>
<%= devise_error_messages! %>
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-lg-4"></div>
  <div class="col-lg-2">
    <%= f.label :first_name %>
    <%= f.text_field :first_name, style: "width: 100%;", :autofocus => true %>
  </div> <div class="col-lg-2">
  <%= f.label :last_name %>
  <%= f.text_field :last_name, style: "width: 100%;" %>
</div>
</div>

<br>

<div class="row">
  <div class="col-lg-4"></div>
  <div class="col-lg-4">
    <%= f.label :email %><br />
    <%= f.email_field :email, style: "width: 100%;" %>
  </div>
</div>

<br>

<div class="row">
  <div class="col-lg-4"></div>
  <div class="col-lg-4">
    <%= f.label :password %><br />
    <%= f.password_field :password, style: "width: 100%;" %>
  </div>
</div>
<br>
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-lg-4"></div>
  <div class="col-lg-4">
    <%= f.label :password_confirmation %><br />
    <%= f.password_field :password_confirmation, style: "width: 100%;" %>
  </div>
</div>
<br>
<div class="row">
   <div class="col-lg-4"></div>
  <div class="col-lg-4">
    <%= f.submit "Sign up", class: "btn btn-large btn-primary", style: "width: 100%;"%>
<br>
<br>
  <% end %>

  <%= render "devise/shared/links" %>
  </div>
  </div>

  <h3>When you join Komodo, you become a dragon.</h3>
  <p>Nothing will stand in your way when it comes to Komodo. The community of care that is created when you start Komodo immediately begins working in your favor. Need immediate, emergency access to your records? Done. Need to ship those records to a babysitter? Done. This is just the beginning.</p>
